Great! To download all employee data as a CSV file when a button is clicked, follow these steps:


---

1. Add Download Button in HTML

Place this in your get-all-employee.component.html, preferably above or below your table:

<button (click)="downloadCSV()" class="download-button">Download CSV</button>


---

2. Add Logic in get-all-employee.component.ts

Update your component with this method:

downloadCSV(): void {
  const header = ['ID', 'Name', 'Department', 'Salary'];
  const rows = this.filteredList.map(emp => [
    emp.id,
    emp.name,
    emp.department,
    emp.salary
  ]);

  const csvContent =
    [header, ...rows]
      .map(row => row.map(field => `"${field}"`).join(','))
      .join('\n');

  const blob = new Blob([csvContent], { type: 'text/csv;charset=utf-8;' });
  const link = document.createElement('a');
  link.href = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
  link.download = 'employee-data.csv';
  link.click();
}


---

3. (Optional) Style the Button in get-all-employee.component.css

.download-button {
  margin-bottom: 10px;
  padding: 6px 12px;
  background-color: #4CAF50;
  color: white;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 4px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.download-button:hover {
  background-color: #45a049;
}


---

This will download all filtered records (including search results). If you want to download only all DB data, not filtered, change this.filteredList to this.employees.

